Pronombres Interrogativos:

Las preposiciones van al final de la pregunta.

who : quién
whose:de quién
wich: cuál
what: qué.

PronombreInterrogativo aux sujeto verbo preposición.

Whose book is this ?
What is she crying about ?
Where do you come from ? 

Some: alguno,alguna. En oraciones positivas.
Any: alguno,alguna . En oraciones negativas o preguntas.
-anyone (alguno,ninguno), anything (cualquier cosa),anywhere ( cualquier lugar)

He has some friends there
He hasn't any friends there.

I heard someone in the next room
I didn't hear anyone in the next room

who: quien
whom: a quien
whose : cuyo

The man whom you saw yesterday, was my brother.
The man who called , was an engineer.
The man whose sister you met yersterday, is here now.
( el hombre cuya hermana conociste ayer, está aquí ahora) 

Pronombres reflexivos.

myself
yourself
himself
herself
itself
ourselves
yourselves
themselves

Pronombres posesivos

(mio,tuyo,suya,nuestro,de ustedes,vuesto,de ellos)

mine
yours
his
hers
ours
yours
theirs

The girl herself can do it.
He hurt himself

Pronombres objetivo o acusativo

me 
you
him
her
it
