TAG ENDINGS

you don't believe it , do you ?
The theacher arrived on time, didn't he ?
Jhon can speak English well, can't he ?
The train leaves at noon , doesn't it ?
He is a good student , isn't he ?
He is not a bad teacher, is he ?


TO WISH

I wish I had a car - ojalá tuviera un auto
I wish I had done it in time - Ojalá la hubiera echo a tiempo
I wish it would stop raining - Ojalá pare de llover.
I wish you wouldn't say that again - Le ruego que no vuelva a decir eso.
I wish you would pay attention to what I say - Les ruego que presten atencion a lo que digo.

SAY , TELL 

Tell : me dijo, le dijo
Say: tal persona dijo .

Maria said that she was tired.

The theacher said "Marcelo"

Maria told me that she was tired.


WOULD RATHER - HAD BETTER

Actúan como auxiliares, y van seguidas del verbo en infinitivo sin TO. Se usan en presente o futuro.

Se contraen con 'd

Would rather: prefiero
Had better: es conveniente.


I would rather stay home // prefiero quedarme en casa

They had better pay attention to the teacher // les conviene poner atención al maestro.

He'd better study the lesson // Les convendría estudiar la lección


He'd rather read than watch tv/ / El prefiere leer que mirar TV

SOO, TOO, EITHER, NEITHER

Se usan con los auxiliares.

He speaks English well and I do too
-- el habla inglés bien  y yo también
They went there and we did too .
They went there and so did we.

--ellos fueron allí y nosotros también

En las negativas se usa EITHER y NEITHER (tampoco)

They didn't go there and we didn't either

They didn't go there and neither did we.

Con neither el auxiliar queda afirmativo.
